title: Chassis
description: Main chassis structure of the machine, contains the frame and the base.

description: Connects the structure to the base and the sliding pipes.

title: Column head
description: Connects the three pipe ends together, also the belt should attach to it.

description: Holds one of the two horizontal pipes.

title: Bracket support
description: Connects the horizontal pipe brackets to the vertical pipe bracket.

description: Connects the column to the base and provides a regulation screw to adjust the heigth.

title: Metallic finger
description: Steel finger to move the pipe up for adjustment.

title: Base assembly
description: MDF board with holes and threaded inserts.

title: M8 Wood Threaded Insert
description: Threaded insert for wood sheets, OD 26mm

title: Side assembly
description: The pipe where the slider rolls. Holds the belt clamps.

title: Belt clamp assembly
description: The assembly of the belt clamp.

title: Belt clamp
description: Holds to the pipe and clamps the belt.

title: X and Y slider
description: Move the gantry in the XY plane.

description: Spring that attaches to the slider body and maintains contact with the pipe.

title: Belt guard
description: Prevent the misalignment of the belt.

title: Motor assembly
description: Motor mount that attaches over the slider assembly.

description: Connector to the vaccum and brushe

description: Main piece of the XY slider.

description: Main piece of the Z slider.
